Description: Limestone stela of Seneferseshempepy: this panel, which is carved in good sunk relief of provincial style, comes from the tomb of Neferseshempepy who had the 'good name' Snnỉ. The deceased owner is represented, dressed in official uniform, carrying staff and sceptre, striding forward. Above his figure and to its left are five lines of text containing a ḥtp-dỉ-nsw text and the titles of Neferseshempepy. The signs are carved with considerable accomplishment, having much internal detail, although their style is somewhat gauche. No colour remains.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: B. Porter & R. Moss, 'Topographical Bibliography of Ancient Egyptian Hieroglyphic Texts, Reliefs and Paintings' V (Oxford: Clarendon Press), p. 112.
